      • insertFeatures

        public void insertFeatures​(FeatureCursor features)
                    throws DataStoreException
        Description copied from interface: FeatureDataStore2
        Performs bulk insertion of the specified features.
        Specified by:
        insertFeatures in interface FeatureDataStore2
        Overrides:
        insertFeatures in class AbstractFeatureDataStore3
        Parameters:
        features - The features to be inserted. Each feature must have its feature set ID set to a valid value. If the feature ID is FeatureDataStore2.FEATURE_ID_NONE, the data store will assign a unique ID; if the feature version is FeatureDataStore2.FEATURE_VERSION_NONE, a version of 1L will be assigned.
        Throws:
        DataStoreException - If an error occurs with the underlying data store (e.g. IO error writing the feature to some persistent storage) during insert.
